testmd

Class Permutation

  • java.lang.Object
    • testmd.Permutation

  • public class Permutation
extends Object
    Defines a test permutation to execute. New permutation objects created through TestMD.permutation() or TestMD.permutation(java.util.Map) ) to ensure that they are property managed for saving results.

    The lifecycle of a permutation is to call:
    1. A previous run (if any) is looked up by comparing the values stored in addParameter(String, Object) with previous runs
    2. If a previous run is found and it was "verified", the values from addResult(String, Object) are compared with the previous run and if the results are the same this test is assumed to be correct still and finished.
    3. The Setup implementation defined by setup(testmd.logic.Setup).
    4. If the Setup object pass, the Verification test defined by run(testmd.logic.Verification) is executed
    5. If run throws exceptions, the results are not saved and the test fails. If all permutations pass the results are saved for future tests.
    6. Regardless of Setup and Verification, the Cleanup object defined by cleanup(testmd.logic.Cleanup) is executed


    Format and additional information in the saved results can be managed with addNote(String, Object) and asTable(java.util.Collection)
